        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the third year of his sojourn at Zarephath the word of the Lord came to Elijah to show himself to Ahab; since God was about to send rain upon the land again. The time given, \"the third year,\" is not to be reckoned, as the Rabbins, Clericus, Thenius, and others assume, from the commencement of the drought, but from the event last mentioned, namely, the sojourn of Elijah at Zarephath. This view merits the preference as the simplest and most natural one, and is shown to be the oldest by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 4:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "James 5:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where Christ and James both say, that in the time of Ahab it did not rain for three years and six months. And this length of time can only be obtained by allowing more than two years for Elijah's stay at Zarephath. -  From ",
        "children": []
      },
